The paper deals with image manipulation detection using deep learning features and adversarial attacks, which are common topics in computer vision (cs.CV) and cybersecurity (cs.CR). The use of random feature selection to improve the robustness of detectors is a machine learning technique (cs.LG), and the study of attack transferability is also relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
